theorem closure_inter_interior_subset_closure_inter {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) ∩ interior (B : Set X) ⊆ closure (A ∩ B : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  rcases hx with ⟨hx_clA, hx_intB⟩
  -- We show that `x` is a limit point of `A ∩ B`.
  -- Unfold the definition of `closure`.
  rw mem_closure_iff at hx_clA ⊢
  intro U hU_open hxU
  -- Intersect the neighbourhood `U` with `interior B`, which is itself open.
  have h_open : IsOpen (U ∩ interior (B : Set X)) := hU_open.inter isOpen_interior
  have hxUV : x ∈ U ∩ interior (B : Set X) := ⟨hxU, hx_intB⟩
  -- Since `x ∈ closure A`, this new open set meets `A`.
  have h_nonempty : ((U ∩ interior (B : Set X)) ∩ A).Nonempty :=
    hx_clA _ h_open hxUV
  -- Any point in this intersection is in `A ∩ B` and still in `U`.
  rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, ⟨hyU, hy_intB⟩, hyA⟩
  have hyB : y ∈ (B : Set X) := interior_subset hy_intB
  exact ⟨y, ⟨hyU, ⟨hyA, hyB⟩⟩⟩

theorem P2_union_interior_right {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A → Topology.P2 (A ∪ interior (B : Set X)) := by
  intro hP2A
  have hOpenInt : IsOpen (interior (B : Set X)) := isOpen_interior
  exact
    (Topology.P2_union_right_of_open
      (X := X) (A := A) (B := interior (B : Set X))) hP2A hOpenInt
